cs.LO, cs.AI, cs.SE, cs.PL, cs.LG

This paper involves the combination of statistical machine learning and symbolic methods for proof-pattern recognition and lemma discovery in the ACL2 theorem prover. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). Additionally, the paper involves the use of statistical pattern recognition, which falls under the sub-category cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also involves software engineering aspects, such as the implementation of the ACL2(ml) tool, which could place it under cs.SE (Software Engineering). The use of symbolic methods for lemma discovery could also place it under cs.PL (Programming Languages). Finally, the paper involves the use of statistical methods, which could place it under cs.LG (Machine Learning).
